==English==
===Etymology===
There are many theories as to where this idiom comes from, but more plausible one would be as follows:
#A person standing on a [[pail]] or [[bucket]] with her head in a [[slip noose]] would kick the bucket so as to [[commit suicide]];

===Verbal idiom===
'''[[kick]] the [[bucket]]'''

# {{cattag|Euphemism}} To [[die]]
#: ''The old horse finally '''kicked the bucket'''.''
# {{slang}} Of a machine, to break down such that it cannot be repaired.
#: ''I think my sewing machine has '''kicked the bucket'''.''

